# Scene lighting & fabric balance (locked)

Do **not** retune lighting or fabric materials unless the user explicitly asks. This balance was iterated to completion.

## Scene (`StandCanvas.tsx`)

- Exposure: `toneMappingExposure: 1.3`
- Background: `#525862`
- Cool neutral exhibition hall (not warm apartment): ambient `0.5`, hemisphere `0.55`, key dir `0.82`, fill `0.34`, ceiling dir `0.4`
- Environment: `studio` preset, `environmentIntensity: 0.48`
- **No** render-layer tricks on the camera or floor

## Floor (`Floor.tsx`, `floorMaterials.ts`)

- Default layer 0 only — no `FLOOR_LAYER` separation
- `meshLambertMaterial`: `map` + `emissiveMap` (same texture), `toneMapped={false}`, `envMap={null}`
- `FLOOR_DIFFUSE_TINT #ffffff`, `FLOOR_EMISSIVE_INTENSITY 0.2`, `FLOOR_AO_INTENSITY 0.18`
- No floor-only rect/hemisphere lights (they spilled onto fabrics)

## Artwork on fabric (`fabricMaterials.tsx`)

- **Always** `meshBasicMaterial` + `toneMapped={false}` — never `meshStandardMaterial` on uploaded images
- Luminous **off**: `ARTWORK_RESTING_COLOR` (`#737373`) — dim, accurate hues, no scene wash
- Luminous **on**: `ARTWORK_LUMINOUS_COLOR` (`#ffffff`) — full print brightness
- Do **not** add emissive/transmission/`emissiveMap` to artwork materials

## Luminous fabric

- Glow lives **only** in `fabricLuminousBacklight.tsx` (core + bloom + rect area light behind panel)
- Use `getInteriorLocalZOffset()` for backing/glow placement — never fixed `-Z` offsets on rotated front faces
- Tune via `fabricLuminous.ts` constants only; keep artwork material unchanged when toggling luminous

## Block-out fabric

- Face: unlit `meshBasicMaterial` `#6a6a6a`
- Backing: `fabricBlockout.tsx`, interior-side offset, `FrontSide`/`BackSide` (not `DoubleSide` on front faces)
- Backing render order behind fabric face

## Anti-patterns (caused regressions)

- `meshStandardMaterial` on artwork under bright scene lights → white wash
- Uniform emissive or transmission on artwork → wash-out
- Floor on render layer 1 + camera layer enable → invisible floor / fabric artifacts
- Warm env preset or warm key light → luminous reads as lamps not LED panels
- Block-out backing at wrong local Z on Y=π panels → extra visible layer on front
